name: Green Bay Packers at Detroit Lions

headlines.description: — Dan Campbell's gambles paid off.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dan Campbell's 4th-down gambles help Lions beat Packers 34-31 and clinch playoffs

name: Jacksonville Jaguars at Tennessee Titans

headlines.description: — If misery loves company, the Jacksonville Jaguars made sure they have just that at the bottom of the AFC South.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jaguars score final 10 points, end Titans' slim playoff hopes with 10-6 win

name: New York Jets at Miami Dolphins

headlines.description: — Tua Tagovailoa wouldn't want to repeat everything that was said in the Miami Dolphins' huddle Sunday when they trailed the New York Jets in the fourth quarter.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tua Tagovailoa's TD pass to Jonnu Smith gives Dolphins 32-26 overtime win over Aaron Rodgers, Jets

name: Atlanta Falcons at Minnesota Vikings

headlines.description: — Sam Darnold tossed aside his stoic demeanor for a moment after realizing he was on the videoboard, aggressively twirling a towel to further stoke the crowd's fire after the Minnesota Vikings had...
headlines.shortLinkText: Darnold delivers for Vikings with career-high 347 yards and 5 TDs to beat Falcons, Cousins 42-21

name: New Orleans Saints at New York Giants

headlines.description: — The New Orleans Saints took two leaps against the New York Giants. One by defensive tackle Bryan Bresee saved a much-needed win. The other by quarterback Derek Carr may have damaged their already slim chances of winning the NFC South.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bresee blocks potential tying FG and Saints hold on to beat Giants 14-11 after Carr is injured

name: Carolina Panthers at Philadelphia Eagles

headlines.description: — The mood in the Eagles' locker room was a bit more bleak than it should have been for a team riding a nine-game winning streak and celebrating a franchise rushing record.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barkley's brilliance helps Eagles beat Panthers 22-16 but pass game has Philly frustrated

name: Cleveland Browns at Pittsburgh Steelers

headlines.description: — Cam Heyward has been on good teams before. Ones that have captured divisions. Ones that have won playoff games, though admittedly not in a while.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wilson throws for 2 touchdowns as Steelers cruise past mistake-prone Browns 27-14

name: Las Vegas Raiders at Tampa Bay Buccaneers

headlines.description: — The surging Tampa Bay Buccaneers are back over .500, a fourth straight NFC South title within reach.
headlines.shortLinkText: Baker Mayfield throws for 3 TDs, Bucs take over 1st in NFC South with 28-13 win over Raiders

name: Seattle Seahawks at Arizona Cardinals

headlines.description: — On a play that didn't particularly matter in the final seconds of the fourth quarter, Seattle's defense was swarming anyway, chasing Arizona's Kyler Murray across the field before the quarterback dejectedly slid to the ground for a sack as the clock...
headlines.shortLinkText: Charbonnet runs for career-high 134 yards, 2 TDs as NFC West-leading Seahawks beat Cardinals 30-18

name: Buffalo Bills at Los Angeles Rams

headlines.description: — Matthew Stafford and the Los Angeles Rams had to pile up a veritable mountain of points, yards and time-of-possession advantage early on to give themselves even a chance against the Buffalo Bills' ferocious fourth-quarter rally and a historic...
headlines.shortLinkText: Allen sets NFL mark with 3 TD passes and 3 TD runs, but Stafford's Rams hold off Bills 44-42

name: Chicago Bears at San Francisco 49ers

headlines.description: — After weeks of shaky play, the San Francisco 49ers got back to their old form with one of the most dominant first halves in years.
headlines.shortLinkText: 49ers beat the Bears 38-13 to spoil Thomas Brown's coaching debut

name: Los Angeles Chargers at Kansas City Chiefs

headlines.description: — Andy Reid doesn't need to schedule a stress test anytime soon. He seems to get one every week.
headlines.shortLinkText: Chiefs win 9th straight AFC West title, beating Chargers 19-17 on bank-shot field goal

name: Cincinnati Bengals at Dallas Cowboys

headlines.description: — Joe Burrow and the Cincinnati Bengals finally got a break.
headlines.shortLinkText: Burrow, Chase lift Bengals after botched blocked punt by Cowboys in 27-20 Cincinnati victory

name: Los Angeles Rams at San Francisco 49ers

headlines.description: — Four nights after winning the highest-scoring game of the NFL season, the Los Angeles Rams won the only game this year that didn't have a touchdown.
headlines.shortLinkText: The Rams get 4 field goals to beat the 49ers 12-6 in a sloppy game

name: Kansas City Chiefs at Cleveland Browns

headlines.description: — The only thing the Chiefs had to worry about in the final minutes Sunday was Patrick Mahomes' ankle.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mahomes throws 2 TD passes, leaves with ankle injury in Chiefs' 21-7 win. X-rays negative on star QB

name: Cincinnati Bengals at Tennessee Titans

headlines.description: — Joe Burrow knows the Cincinnati Bengals' playoff hopes are slender at best at the bottom of the AFC's bubble teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Joe Burrow sets franchise record with 3 more TD passes as Bengals beat Titans 37-27

name: Washington Commanders at New Orleans Saints

headlines.description: — Jayden Daniels' second game in the Superdome again came down to a play after a touchdown with no time left.
headlines.shortLinkText: Daniels passes for 2 TDs and Commanders outlast Saints 20-19 on New Orleans' failed 2-point try

name: Baltimore Ravens at New York Giants

headlines.description: — Lamar Jackson was miffed after losing a fumble at the Giants 12-yard line on the second play from scrimmage, and the Baltimore Ravens' superstar quarterback took it out on New York the rest of the day.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson throws 5 TD passes and Ravens send Giants to franchise record-tying 9th straight loss, 35-14

name: Dallas Cowboys at Carolina Panthers

headlines.description: — CeeDee Lamb heard about oddsmakers listing the Carolina Panthers as a favorite for the first time in nearly two full years entering Sunday's game against the Dallas Cowboys.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rush throws for career-high 3 TDs, Cowboys force 4 turnovers to beat Panthers 30-14

name: New York Jets at Jacksonville Jaguars

headlines.description: — Davante Adams and Aaron Rodgers gave the New York Jets' next general manager and head coach something to ponder with a glimpse into the past — and potentially the future.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vintage performances by Davante Adams and Aaron Rodgers carry Jets past defenseless Jaguars 32-25

name: Miami Dolphins at Houston Texans

headlines.description: — Tasked with shadowing Miami's star receiver Tyreek Hill for most of Sunday's game, Houston cornerback Derek Stingley shined.
headlines.shortLinkText: Collins has 2 TD catches, Texans force 4 turnovers in 20-12 win over Dolphins

name: Indianapolis Colts at Denver Broncos

headlines.description: — Nik Bonitto's defensive touchdown was jaw-dropping. Jonathan Taylor's botched touchdown run was head-scratching.
headlines.shortLinkText: Broncos roar back on the strength of 5 takeaways to beat Colts 31-13 and close in on playoff berth

name: Buffalo Bills at Detroit Lions

headlines.description: — Josh Allen took a shotgun snap, moved up in the pocket and backed up, rolled left and threw right.
headlines.shortLinkText: Josh Allen has another huge game to lift Bills to a 48-42 victory that snaps Lions' winning streak

name: Pittsburgh Steelers at Philadelphia Eagles

headlines.description: — Jalen Hurts absorbed the shots when the Eagles' recent anemic passing attack was panned by his own star wide receivers. Hurts and A.J. Brown — one of those receivers who brought the complaints to a boil — then had their relationship dissected and...
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Hurts accounts for 3 TDs and Eagles beat Steelers 27-13 for franchise-best 10th straight win

name: New England Patriots at Arizona Cardinals

headlines.description: — Just five plays into Sunday's game, the Arizona Cardinals had lost two starting linebackers to injury.
headlines.shortLinkText: James Conner runs for 2 TDs and Cardinals snap a 3-game skid by beating Patriots 30-17

name: Tampa Bay Buccaneers at Los Angeles Chargers

headlines.description: — Two years ago, Baker Mayfield was trying to salvage his career in Southern California.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mayfield throws for 4 TD passes as Buccaneers dominate the second half to rout Chargers 40-17

name: Green Bay Packers at Seattle Seahawks

headlines.description: — Romeo Doubs improbably pulled in his second touchdown catch of the night from Jordan Love, sealing a decisive victory for the Packers and moving them closer to the postseason.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jordan Love throws for 2 TDs and Packers beat Seahawks 30-13 as Seattle QB Geno Smith injures knee

name: Chicago Bears at Minnesota Vikings

headlines.description: — Their spot in the playoffs secure, the Minnesota Vikings delivered a prime-time performance seeped in those ingredients that frequently fuel postseason success.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vikings win 7th straight to forge tie for NFC North lead with 30-12 blowout of reeling Bears

name: Atlanta Falcons at Las Vegas Raiders

headlines.description: — Ahead most of the game, including by double digits in the fourth quarter, the Atlanta Falcons were just trying to hold on at the end.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cousins and Falcons do just enough to beat Raiders 15-9 and keep pace with Bucs in NFC South

name: Denver Broncos at Los Angeles Chargers

headlines.description: — Trailing 21-13 at halftime Thursday night against the Denver Broncos, some wondered if the Los Angeles Chargers had any resolve left after going through their worst four-quarter stretch of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Justin Herbert passes for 2 touchdowns, Chargers score on free kick and rally past Broncos 34-27

name: Houston Texans at Kansas City Chiefs

headlines.description: — Patrick Mahomes knew he could run on the ankle he sprained last week. The bigger concern for the Chiefs quarterback was how he would stop, when all the weight and pressure and momentum would land squarely upon it.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mahomes throws for TD and runs for score as Chiefs beat Texans 27-19 to close in on No. 1 seed

name: Pittsburgh Steelers at Baltimore Ravens

headlines.description: — Lamar Jackson was solid in Baltimore's biggest game of the season so far.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lamar Jackson and the Ravens draw even atop the AFC North, beating the 1st-place Steelers 34-17

name: New York Giants at Atlanta Falcons

headlines.description: — Michael Penix Jr. felt a brief bit of apprehension as he ran down the tunnel, which was to be expected.
headlines.shortLinkText: Penix wins debut as Atlanta QB as Falcons return two picks for TDs, beat hapless Giants 34-7

name: Detroit Lions at Chicago Bears

headlines.description: — Jared Goff and the Detroit Lions locked in from the start and delivered a bounce-back performance. It came with a few team records, too.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jared Goff throws 3 TD passes as Lions beat Bears 34-17 for franchise-record 13th win

name: Cleveland Browns at Cincinnati Bengals

headlines.description: — Joe Burrow and Ja'Marr Chase keep putting up extraordinary numbers, but the Cincinnati Bengals still need help to reach the playoffs.
headlines.shortLinkText: Burrow throws 3 TD passes and Bengals keep playoff hopes alive with 24-6 victory over Browns

name: Tennessee Titans at Indianapolis Colts

headlines.description: — Jonathan Taylor took matters into his own hands Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jonathan Taylor rebounds with 218 yards, 3 TD runs as Colts hold off Titans 38-30

name: Los Angeles Rams at New York Jets

headlines.description: — Tyler Higbee waited nearly a year for this moment.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stafford's TD pass to Higbee after Rodgers' turnover leads Rams past Jets 19-9

name: Philadelphia Eagles at Washington Commanders

headlines.description: — Jayden Daniels was not worried when he and the Washington Commanders trailed the Philadelphia Eagles by 14 points after just seven minutes, and the rookie quarterback was similarly undaunted staring down a 13-point deficit going into the fourth...
headlines.shortLinkText: Jayden Daniels throws for 5 TDs as the Commanders end the Eagles' winning streak at 10

name: Arizona Cardinals at Carolina Panthers
Minnesota Vikings at Seattle Seahawks

headlines.description: — Sam Darnold has inspired confidence in his coach and teammates throughout this career-changing season. With the Vikings facing another late deficit, they had no doubt he'd deliver.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sam Darnold and Justin Jefferson lead surging Vikings past Seahawks 27-24

name: New England Patriots at Buffalo Bills

headlines.description: — With the Bills' attention and concern focused on the sideline, where trainers were examining quarterback Josh Allen’s throwing arm, cornerback Taron Johnson provided the necessary offense to lift Buffalo to 24-21 win over the New England Patriots on...
headlines.shortLinkText: James Cook scores 2 TDs and Bills force 3 turnovers in 24-21 win over Patriots

name: Jacksonville Jaguars at Las Vegas Raiders

headlines.description: — Raiders owner Mark Davis made the rounds Sunday to congratulate the players as music blared inside the locker room.
headlines.shortLinkText: O'Connell passes for 257 yards and Raiders snap 10-game skid with 19-14 win over Jaguars

name: San Francisco 49ers at Miami Dolphins

headlines.description: — The Miami Dolphins were not ready for their season to be over, even after a disappointing loss at Houston last week that narrowed their faint playoff hopes.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dolphins keep playoff hopes alive with 29-17 win over 49ers, who were eliminated before the game

name: Tampa Bay Buccaneers at Dallas Cowboys

headlines.description: — Baker Mayfield came home to Texas looking to keep his Tampa Bay Buccaneers on track for the playoffs.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cowboys beat Tampa Bay 26-24 as Baker Mayfield and the Bucs lose control of their playoff fate

name: New Orleans Saints at Green Bay Packers

headlines.description: — With a dominant defense leading the way, the Green Bay Packers clinched a playoff berth by producing their most lopsided win in a decade.
headlines.shortLinkText: Packers clinch playoff berth with 1st shutout in NFL this season, 34-0 over Saints

name: Kansas City Chiefs at Pittsburgh Steelers

headlines.description: — Andy Reid donned a Santa Claus suit in a giddy Kansas City Chiefs locker room on Christmas Day, then handed his team a present it increasingly looks like it deserves: home-field...
headlines.shortLinkText: Mahomes throws 3 TDs as Chiefs clinch AFC's top seed by breezing past the skidding Steelers 29-10

name: Baltimore Ravens at Houston Texans

headlines.description: — Lamar Jackson broke the NFL career rushing record for quarterbacks in the Baltimore Ravens' victory over the Houston Texans on Wednesday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lamar Jackson breaks NFL QB rushing record, accounts for 3 TDs in Ravens' 31-2 romp over Texans

name: Seattle Seahawks at Chicago Bears

headlines.description: — The Seattle Seahawks made just enough plays to boost their fading playoff hopes by beating the struggling Chicago Bears on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Woolen's late interception seals win as Seahawks beat struggling Bears 6-3 to boost playoff hopes

name: Los Angeles Chargers at New England Patriots

headlines.description: — As spontaneous celebrations rippled throughout the Los Angeles Chargers' locker room after their resounding 40-7 win over the New England Patriots, coach Jim Harbaugh grabbed...
headlines.shortLinkText: Herbert tosses 3 TD passes and Chargers secure a playoff spot with a 40-7 rout of Patriots

name: Denver Broncos at Cincinnati Bengals

headlines.description: — This time, near the very end of a mostly agonizing season, the Cincinnati Bengals made enough plays to win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Burrow throws 3-yard TD pass to Higgins in OT as the Bengals beat the Broncos 30-24

name: Arizona Cardinals at Los Angeles Rams

headlines.description: — The Los Angeles Rams spent the entire second half struggling on offense while bending just enough on defense to preserve a tiny lead.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ahkello Witherspoon makes last-minute interception to preserve Rams' 13-9 win over Arizona

name: New York Jets at Buffalo Bills

headlines.description: — Josh Allen reflected on Buffalo’s many offseason critics and doubters when asked about the Bills achieving their latest milestones while sewing up the AFC’s No. 2 seed with a 40-14 rout of the unraveling and undisciplined New York Jets on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bills clinch the AFC's No. 2 seed with a 40-14 rout of the undisciplined Jets

name: Las Vegas Raiders at New Orleans Saints

headlines.description: — Aidan O'Connell and the Las Vegas Raiders played with a lot of energy — and looked pretty sharp — for a last-place team that had every excuse to be sluggish and sleep-deprived.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brock Bowers sets NFL rookie records as the Raiders roll to a 25-10 victory over the Saints

name: Indianapolis Colts at New York Giants

headlines.description: — Snapping a franchise-record 10-game losing streak, winning for the first time at home this season and ending the Indianapolis Colts' slim playoff hopes Sunday didn't salvage the season for the New York Giants.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giants topple Colts 45-33 to eliminate Indy from the playoff race

name: Dallas Cowboys at Philadelphia Eagles

headlines.description: — Nick Sirianni wore the hat given to NFC East champions as he sat at the podium and considered all the greatness that his Eagles still could accomplish this season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Saquon Barkley tops 2,000 yards rushing as Eagles beat Cowboys 41-7 to clinch NFC East

name: Carolina Panthers at Tampa Bay Buccaneers

headlines.description: — The Tampa Bay Buccaneers played like a team determined to do whatever's necessary to make the playoffs.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mayfield throws 5 TD passes and Bucs keep playoff, NFC South hopes alive with 48-14 rout of Panthers

name: Tennessee Titans at Jacksonville Jaguars

headlines.description: — Whoever ends up coaching the Jacksonville Jaguars next season, receiver Brian Thomas Jr. will be the team's most dynamic rebuilding piece.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rookie Brian Thomas Jr. scores again as Jaguars beat Titans 20-13 for rare series sweep

name: Miami Dolphins at Cleveland Browns

headlines.description: — Tyler Huntley stepped in for Tua Tagovailoa and stepped up for the Dolphins.
headlines.shortLinkText: Huntley fills in for injured Tagovailoa, leads Dolphins past Browns 20-3 to keep playoff hopes alive

name: Green Bay Packers at Minnesota Vikings

headlines.description: — The Minnesota Vikings were ready to start their postgame ritual in honor of a ninth consecutive victory before realizing Sam Darnold was still missing from the <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Darnold gives Vikings another gem with career-high 377 yards in 27-25 win over Packers

name: Atlanta Falcons at Washington Commanders

headlines.description: — Jayden Daniels felt tired. Tired from a game that went well past 60 minutes. Tired from running all over the field for the better part of three-plus hours.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jayden Daniels dazzles again as Commanders clinch a playoff spot by beating Falcons 30-24 in OT

name: Detroit Lions at San Francisco 49ers

headlines.description: — The big prizes for the Detroit Lions remain on the horizon, with the team seeking a division title, the top seed in the NFC playoffs and the franchise's first Super Bowl trip.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lions beat the 49ers 40-34 in a tune-up for Week 18 division showdown

name: Cleveland Browns at Baltimore Ravens

headlines.description: — Lamar Jackson threw two touchdown passes, and the Baltimore Ravens won the AFC North for the second straight season, clinching the division with a 35-10 victory over the Cleveland Browns on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ravens wrap up the AFC North with a 35-10 rout of Cleveland; Jackson surpasses 4,000 yards passing

name: Cincinnati Bengals at Pittsburgh Steelers

headlines.description: — Joe Burrow will head to Cincinnati's training facility on Sunday. He'll lift weights. He might watch some video. And then he'll join the rest of his teammates and hope.
headlines.shortLinkText: Joe Burrow and the Cincinnati Bengals keep their playoff hopes alive by edging the Steelers 19-17

name: Carolina Panthers at Atlanta Falcons

headlines.description: — The Atlanta Falcons and Carolina Panthers have more in common than frustrating streaks of seven consecutive losing seasons.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bryce Young accounts for 5 TDs as Panthers beat Falcons 44-38 in OT. Atlanta misses playoffs again

name: Washington Commanders at Dallas Cowboys

headlines.description: — Jayden Daniels sitting in the second half wasn’t the plan when the playoff-bound Washington Commanders visited the Dallas Cowboys with only seeding at stake.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mariota leads playoff-bound Commanders to 23-19 win over Cowboys after replacing Daniels

name: Chicago Bears at Green Bay Packers

headlines.description: — Caleb Williams gained a shot of confidence and Cairo Santos earned a measure of redemption.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bears rally for 24-22 win in Green Bay as Packers lose Love and Watson to injuries

name: Houston Texans at Tennessee Titans

headlines.description: — The Houston Texans gave what coach DeMeco Ryans wanted from their trip to Music City.
headlines.shortLinkText: Playoff-bound Texans cruise to 23-14 win over the Titans, who land No. 1 draft pick

name: Jacksonville Jaguars at Indianapolis Colts

headlines.description: — Jonathan Taylor closed the season with a flourish. Joe Flacco may have walked off the field for the final time as a winner.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jonathan Taylor and Joe Flacco lead Colts to 26-23 overtime win over Jaguars

name: Buffalo Bills at New England Patriots

headlines.description: — The New England Patriots concluded a bitter season on a high note.
headlines.shortLinkText: Patriots beat Bills 23-16 to cost themselves top draft pick. Coach Jerod Mayo fired after game

name: New York Giants at Philadelphia Eagles

headlines.description: — Saquon Barkley traded his No. 26 jersey for a T-shirt that celebrated his 2,000 yards rushing this season and Jalen Hurts remained sidelined with a concussion.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barkley and Hurts sit as the Eagles tune up for the playoffs with a 20-13 win over the Giants

name: New Orleans Saints at Tampa Bay Buccaneers

headlines.description: — Just 36 seconds away from clinching the NFC South title, the Tampa Bay Buccaneers had another goal to achieve.
headlines.shortLinkText: Buccaneers beat Saints 27-19 to clinch NFC South and wide receiver Mike Evans surpasses 1,000 yards

name: Kansas City Chiefs at Denver Broncos

headlines.description: — Bo Nix celebrated the end of Denver's eight-year playoff drought with a bunch of new friends.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nix leads Broncos past Chiefs' reserves 38-0 and into playoffs for 1st time since 2015 season

name: Los Angeles Chargers at Las Vegas Raiders

headlines.description: — Chargers quarterback Justin Herbert said he could tell from the noise his teammates made from neighboring meeting rooms on Saturday “that good things were happening.”
headlines.shortLinkText: Justin Herbert and Chargers secure AFC's No. 5 seed with 34-20 win over Raiders

name: Seattle Seahawks at Los Angeles Rams

headlines.description: — Matthew Stafford and nearly all of his fellow offensive starters watched the Los Angeles Rams' regular-season finale in street clothes. Coach Sean McVay knew his NFC West champions would fall from the third to the fourth playoff seed if they lost to...
headlines.shortLinkText: Geno Smith throws career-high 4 TD passes in Seahawks' 30-25 win over playoff-bound Rams

name: Miami Dolphins at New York Jets

headlines.description: — Aaron Rodgers walked off the field with his buddy Davante Adams by his side, waved his left hand to the New York Jets fans cheering his name in the MetLife Stadium stands and walked through the dark tunnel to the locker room.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rodgers throws a season-high 4 touchdown passes in possible final game as Jets top Dolphins 32-20

name: San Francisco 49ers at Arizona Cardinals

headlines.description: — The Cardinals' final passing touchdown of the season was a perfectly placed ball from Kyler Murray to rookie Marvin Harrison Jr. — a 12-yard strike in the fourth quarter that sealed their 47-24 win over the San Francisco 49ers on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kyler Murray throws 4 TD passes and the Cardinals beat the 49ers 47-24 in finale

name: Minnesota Vikings at Detroit Lions

headlines.description: — Jahmyr Gibbs was the game-breaking player the Detroit Lions needed to get their high-powered offense in gear — and give them a first-round bye and home-field advantage in the NFC playoffs.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lions beat Vikings 31-9, win NFC North and No. 1 seed, dropping division rivals to No. 5
